    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_11_14_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Trim_IE">Trim</placeName>
                        <date when="1841-11-14">Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>14.<hi rend="superscript">h</hi>1841</date></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrJ3">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Murray</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    
                    1 North Audley Street
                    March 1[superscript]t[/superscript] 1841
                    Dear Sir
                    I have before me a note of
                    your daughters apologising
                    for your not coming to see
                    me - you and your son
                    both owe me the courtesy
                    of a visit - which I must
                    have now or never as I
                    have but this week more
                    of London life - But it is
                    not the mere ceremony of visit
                    ing upon which I stand; I
                    w[superscript]d[/superscript] not take you from solid
                    business to empty morning
                    visit - But I want to see
                    I want to see
                    you both or either to have
                    a half hours [underline]talk[/underline] with you
                    upon a literary project of
                    my friend Madame Bellois
                    -It is not about a book
                    But tho I tell what it is not
                    about I cannot tell you what
                    it is about till [deletion]you[/deletion] we can talk
                    it over - It is too long for
                    
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_11_14_page02.jpg"/>
                    
                    
                    writing notes upon
                    I trust that either you or
                    your son understand
                    French & whichever under
                    stands it best had best
                    read Madame Bellois
                    letter - or [unclear][/unclear] to the
                    translation of
                    D[superscript]r[/superscript] [/superscript]- <closer>Sir yours truly
                    Maria Edgeworth</closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p> [underline]P.S[/underline] Do not come to day!
                            [deletion][unclear]even if you could[/unclear][deletion] because
                            I am engaged all morning
                            till four
                            
                            <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_11_14_page03.jpg"/>
                            
                            / Monday, unless you could come
                            between 4 and 5 </p>
                    </postscript>
                   
                    
                  you could come
                    between 4 and 5
                
                 
                
            </div>
